  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations to Indiana totaled $2.7B in FY2026 to date across 13,491 awards with an average award size of $203K. Obligations fell 60.8% year over year, and current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). Recent fiscal-year totals show variation: FY21 was $6.3B, FY22 was $8.2B, FY23 was $6B, FY24 was $5.3B, and FY25 was $7B, before the FY26 to date total of $2.7B. The Department of Defense accounted for the largest single share in FY2026 to date at $1.9B, followed by other agencies including the Department of Homeland Security at $205M and the Department of Health and Human Services at $168M. Top suppliers include ROLLS-ROYCE CORPORATION at $587M and UNDERSEA SENSOR SYSTEMS, INC. at $243M. Leading industry categories by obligations in FY2026 to date include Aircraft Engine and Engine Parts Manufacturing at $551M and Search, Detection, Navigation, Guidance, Aeronautical, and Nautical System and Instrument Manufacturing at $331M.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How has federal contracting in Indiana changed recently?",
        "body": "Obligations fell 60.8% year over year in FY2026 to date. Fiscal-year totals were $6.3B in FY21, $8.2B in FY22, $6B in FY23, $5.3B in FY24, and $7B in FY25, compared with $2.7B in FY26 to date. Award count in FY2026 to date is 13,491 with an average award size of $203K."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and vendors account for most Indiana obligations?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense is the largest buying agency in FY2026 to date at $1.9B. Other top buying agencies include the Department of Homeland Security at $205M and the Department of Health and Human Services at $168M, while top vendors include ROLLS-ROYCE CORPORATION at $587M and UNDERSEA SENSOR SYSTEMS, INC. at $243M."
      }
    ]
  },
